1️⃣ Collect Inputs Dynamically in Service Layer

Instead of extracting manually, we dynamically collect all used inputs into a Map<String, Object>.

public List<AddressModel> searchAddress(AddressSearchConditionsDTO searchConditions) {
    // Collect non-null and non-empty input fields
    Map<String, Object> usedInputs = new HashMap<>();

    if (searchConditions.getAddressCode() != null && !searchConditions.getAddressCode().isEmpty()) {
        usedInputs.put("addressCode", searchConditions.getAddressCode());
    }
    if (searchConditions.getAddress() != null) {
        if (searchConditions.getAddress().getPostalCode() != null && 
            !searchConditions.getAddress().getPostalCode().isEmpty()) {
            usedInputs.put("postalCode", searchConditions.getAddress().getPostalCode());
        }
        if (searchConditions.getAddress().getCharacterSetType() != null) {
            usedInputs.put("characterSetType", searchConditions.getAddress().getCharacterSetType());
        }
    }

    // Perform the search
    List<AddressModel> results = cosmosContainer.queryItems(
        buildQuery(searchConditions),
        new CosmosQueryRequestOptions(),
        AddressModel.class)
        .stream()
        .collect(Collectors.toList());

    // If no results, throw exception with collected inputs
    if (results.isEmpty()) {
        throw new DataNotFoundException("No records found for the given criteria", usedInputs);
    }

    return results;
}

2️⃣ Modify DataNotFoundException to Store Input Fields

import java.util.Map;

public class DataNotFoundException extends RuntimeException {
    private final Map<String, Object> usedInputs;

    public DataNotFoundException(String message, Map<String, Object> usedInputs) {
        super(message);
        this.usedInputs = usedInputs;
    }

    public Map<String, Object> getUsedInputs() {
        return usedInputs;
    }
}

3️⃣ Modify GlobalExceptionHandler to Include Inputs in Error Response

Extract only the inputs that were actually used dynamically from DataNotFoundException.

@ExceptionHandler(DataNotFoundException.class)
public ResponseEntity<ErrorResponseDTO> handleDataNotFoundException(
        DataNotFoundException ex, HttpServletRequest request) {

    // Convert input parameters into error details dynamically
    List<ErrorDetailDTO> errors = ex.getUsedInputs().entrySet()
            .stream()
            .map(entry -> new ErrorDetailDTO(entry.getKey(), "Used in query but no records found"))
            .collect(Collectors.toList());

    return buildErrorResponse(HttpStatus.NOT_FOUND, "Data not found", errors, request);
}

